WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.055 --> 00:00:02.824
(The following content may not be suitable for viewers under 15.)

2
00:00:02.824 --> 00:00:04.625
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:07.034 --> 00:00:10.733
I gave up on wanting to tell my story as I held on.

4
00:00:13.134 --> 00:00:14.374
But if I keep holding on,

5
00:00:15.604 --> 00:00:19.544
I felt like I would never be able to come back to my true self.

6
00:00:24.583 --> 00:00:26.414
Was it that wrong of me to do that?

7
00:00:48.904 --> 00:00:50.304
I was trying not to cry...

8
00:01:00.984 --> 00:01:03.113
I feel apologetic to you the most.

9
00:01:08.653 --> 00:01:10.024
You're drawing a line...

10
00:01:12.564 --> 00:01:13.763
even in this situation.

11
00:01:24.203 --> 00:01:26.004
Now, enough crying along with you.

12
00:01:27.774 --> 00:01:31.013
It's time for me to think about what I should do about this situation.

13
00:01:31.213 --> 00:01:32.284
But before I do,

14
00:01:32.713 --> 00:01:34.254
I need you to tell me your opinion on this.

15
00:01:35.284 --> 00:01:37.054
Are you sure you're not going to regret making this decision?

16
00:01:38.054 --> 00:01:40.593
This drama might do better after you quit.

17
00:01:40.953 --> 00:01:42.593
This happens a lot in this business.

18
00:01:43.364 --> 00:01:44.694
If you endure this,

19
00:01:45.394 --> 00:01:46.963
things might get easier next time.

20
00:01:52.034 --> 00:01:53.373
I might regret my decision.

21
00:01:54.534 --> 00:01:56.603
I might not be able to write again.

22
00:01:58.573 --> 00:02:01.314
But I still don't want to endure it. If I do,

23
00:02:03.444 --> 00:02:06.084
I think it's going to take me a million years to retrieve my pride.

24
00:02:10.483 --> 00:02:12.453
And after a million years, I'll no longer be here.

25
00:02:14.923 --> 00:02:16.863
I want to start writing again before I die.

26
00:02:20.634 --> 00:02:21.634
Okay.

27
00:02:22.263 --> 00:02:23.333
I'll drive you home.

28
00:02:31.543 --> 00:02:36.013
(Temperature of Love)

29
00:02:36.643 --> 00:02:38.543
- Good luck to us all! - Good luck to us all!

30
00:02:39.314 --> 00:02:40.353
Bottoms up.

31
00:02:40.353 --> 00:02:41.714
(Episode 15)

32
00:02:44.353 --> 00:02:46.384
I'd like to express my gratitude...

33
00:02:46.654 --> 00:02:48.453
for everyone's trust and support.

34
00:02:48.654 --> 00:02:50.624
Things have been so hectic for the past couple of days.

35
00:02:51.923 --> 00:02:53.994
Let's not get swayed by emotions, and keep our cool.

36
00:02:54.293 --> 00:02:56.393
I'll see you again after you guys take some rest for two days.

37
00:02:57.103 --> 00:02:58.803
Let's end the night with this last drink.

38
00:02:59.263 --> 00:03:00.434
- Good. - Soup.

39
00:03:00.434 --> 00:03:02.273
- We can do it! - We can do it!

40
00:03:03.203 --> 00:03:04.944
He's interpreting the dish in his own way.

41
00:03:04.944 --> 00:03:07.043
That's why it's a bit spicy.

42
00:03:08.474 --> 00:03:10.583
Everyone has priorities in life.

43
00:03:12.143 --> 00:03:13.814
She is a higher priority to me.

44
00:03:15.154 --> 00:03:17.124
Do I really like him?

45
00:03:18.423 --> 00:03:21.124
Or am I just obsessed with him because I got rejected by him?

46
00:03:22.923 --> 00:03:25.064
How many times am I watching this?

47
00:03:25.994 --> 00:03:27.164
Jung Sun.

48
00:03:28.233 --> 00:03:31.863
I love you with all my heart and soul.

49
00:03:32.134 --> 00:03:34.773
My gosh, what's wrong with you? You stink of sweat.

50
00:03:35.573 --> 00:03:36.643
You smell too.

51
00:03:36.643 --> 00:03:38.803
I know. That's why I'm not hugging you.

52
00:03:42.173 --> 00:03:43.244
(Hong Ah)

53
00:03:43.244 --> 00:03:44.613
Hey, it's Hong Ah.

54
00:03:45.143 --> 00:03:47.853
Now that you've rejected her, I'm finally getting my chance.

55
00:03:48.154 --> 00:03:49.483
You're incredible.

56
00:03:49.884 --> 00:03:51.184
Aren't you upset?

57
00:03:51.483 --> 00:03:53.793
My affection for her is too strong for me to feel upset.

58
00:03:54.154 --> 00:03:55.853
Do you have a woman who makes you feel this way?

59
00:03:58.293 --> 00:03:59.323
Hey, Hong Ah.

60
00:03:59.793 --> 00:04:00.863
I have someone like that too.

61
00:04:04.333 --> 00:04:05.333
(Missed Call: Lee Hyun Soo)

62
00:04:05.763 --> 00:04:06.833
She called me.

63
00:04:08.303 --> 00:04:10.374
(Lee Hyun Soo)

64
00:04:32.163 --> 00:04:33.934
Okay, I'll be right there.

65
00:04:36.463 --> 00:04:38.504
- The receiver cannot answer... - Is she not picking up?

66
00:04:38.634 --> 00:04:39.634
No.

67
00:04:40.273 --> 00:04:42.004
Hong Ah asked me to come over. I'll see you then.

68
00:04:42.004 --> 00:04:43.604
I'm also going to go see her even though she didn't ask me to.

69
00:04:43.744 --> 00:04:44.804
I thought she didn't pick up.

70
00:04:45.174 --> 00:04:47.544
I can't just go home on such a happy day.

71
00:04:47.744 --> 00:04:49.984
I'm at least going to go see if the lights are off at her place.

72
00:04:51.513 --> 00:04:53.143
How romantic.

73
00:04:53.614 --> 00:04:55.884
I'm going to go to your house, and take a shower before I go.

74
00:04:56.184 --> 00:04:57.523
I can't go in this filthy state.

75
00:04:58.884 --> 00:05:00.354
I'm just going to go like this.

76
00:05:03.494 --> 00:05:04.823
He's one confident fellow.

77
00:05:11.864 --> 00:05:13.434
You didn't have to get off.

78
00:05:15.703 --> 00:05:17.044
Thank you for today.

79
00:05:17.804 --> 00:05:21.143
"I'm sorry. I feel apologetic. Thank you."

80
00:05:22.073 --> 00:05:23.783
Don't ever say anything like that to me again.

81
00:05:24.884 --> 00:05:26.143
That's not what I want to hear.

82
00:05:26.884 --> 00:05:29.083
What I want to hear is a different response for my consideration...

83
00:05:30.124 --> 00:05:31.124
towards you.

84
00:05:33.494 --> 00:05:34.494
Mr. Park.

85
00:05:35.393 --> 00:05:37.364
Are you trying to approach me as a man?

86
00:05:39.934 --> 00:05:40.963
Yes.

87
00:05:46.703 --> 00:05:47.773
Thank you.

88
00:05:48.573 --> 00:05:50.104
You just gave me a good laugh.

89
00:05:52.304 --> 00:05:53.314
Good night.

90
00:06:43.763 --> 00:06:45.663
(Jung Sun)

91
00:06:47.634 --> 00:06:48.694
(Are you sleeping?)

92
00:06:48.694 --> 00:06:49.734
Are you sleeping?

93
00:06:51.903 --> 00:06:52.963
No.

94
00:06:53.634 --> 00:06:54.903
Do you want to meet?

95
00:06:57.573 --> 00:06:58.573
I'm scared.

96
00:06:59.573 --> 00:07:01.244
You pushed me away once.

97
00:07:01.744 --> 00:07:03.643
There's no reason why you wouldn't push me away again.

98
00:07:05.744 --> 00:07:08.554
Love requires two people, but I only thought of myself.

99
00:07:13.223 --> 00:07:14.554
I'll think about it.

100
00:07:19.593 --> 00:07:20.994
(Do you want to meet?)

101
00:07:20.994 --> 00:07:21.994
Where are you?

102
00:07:23.963 --> 00:07:25.033
I'm in the neighborhood.

103
00:07:30.374 --> 00:07:31.703
You surprised me.

104
00:07:32.044 --> 00:07:34.643
Then I succeeded. I was trying to surprise you.

105
00:07:35.643 --> 00:07:36.944
Why are you so happy?

106
00:07:37.384 --> 00:07:39.343
I drank with my Good Soup workers.

107
00:07:39.843 --> 00:07:41.854
The restaurant's packed with customers these days.

108
00:07:43.083 --> 00:07:46.794
My worst day turns out to be his best day.

109
00:07:47.523 --> 00:07:49.294
- I'll be right out. - No, don't come outside.

110
00:07:49.393 --> 00:07:50.963
It's too late. It's dangerous to come outside.

111
00:07:51.564 --> 00:07:52.794
Then do you want to come inside?

112
00:07:52.823 --> 00:07:55.434
No, I smell of sweat. I came right after exercising.

113
00:07:58.564 --> 00:07:59.663
Why did you call?

114
00:08:02.033 --> 00:08:03.304
I pressed the wrong button.

115
00:08:04.473 --> 00:08:06.174
You're attractive when you're honest.

116
00:08:06.343 --> 00:08:07.513
You just lost your charm.

117
00:08:11.143 --> 00:08:13.913
I saw your face, so I'll go now.

118
00:08:16.513 --> 00:08:17.884
People really don't change.

119
00:08:20.093 --> 00:08:21.593
I think the same goes for me.

120
00:08:25.163 --> 00:08:26.734
I thought I had changed.

121
00:08:27.663 --> 00:08:28.934
But I guess I was wrong.

122
00:08:31.933 --> 00:08:34.933
I don't wear my T-shirts inside out at home anymore.

123
00:08:35.004 --> 00:08:36.134
I got rid of that habit.

124
00:08:40.643 --> 00:08:41.714
The wind's cold.

125
00:09:12.303 --> 00:09:14.643
I despise stirring up emotions.

126
00:09:16.844 --> 00:09:19.313
I've never confused you.

127
00:09:19.313 --> 00:09:20.813
Why must I be the only one that assures you?

128
00:09:23.553 --> 00:09:25.653
Your problem is that you think too much,

129
00:09:26.954 --> 00:09:28.094
especially about love.

130
00:09:29.793 --> 00:09:31.563
Just do as your heart tells you.

131
00:09:38.834 --> 00:09:39.834
Hong Ah.

132
00:09:41.933 --> 00:09:43.403
Why did you make me wait?

133
00:09:43.403 --> 00:09:44.474
I took a shower.

134
00:09:45.173 --> 00:09:47.244
You're so foolish. Why did you take a shower when we're going to run?

135
00:09:47.443 --> 00:09:48.474
What?

136
00:09:50.484 --> 00:09:52.313
You can't call a fool foolish.

137
00:10:14.234 --> 00:10:15.303
I won.

138
00:10:16.134 --> 00:10:18.374
I'm going to win at everything.

139
00:10:21.813 --> 00:10:23.114
Aren't you going to pack your things?

140
00:10:23.114 --> 00:10:24.643
I can pack my own stuff.

141
00:10:24.913 --> 00:10:26.813
I thought we still had a week before having to move out.

142
00:10:27.084 --> 00:10:28.413
We still have some time.

143
00:10:28.854 --> 00:10:30.084
Where are you going to go?

144
00:10:30.454 --> 00:10:33.494
I'm going to live with my parents, and come to Seoul when I need to.

145
00:10:33.653 --> 00:10:36.293
Or I could just go live at my cousin's house.

146
00:10:38.324 --> 00:10:39.763
Do you want to live at my place?

147
00:10:41.793 --> 00:10:44.933
You were guaranteed a job until the end of this year.

148
00:10:46.464 --> 00:10:48.533
I don't want to burden you.

149
00:10:48.704 --> 00:10:50.673
You're not a burden.

150
00:10:50.673 --> 00:10:52.504
You should stay in Seoul if you want to keep writing.

151
00:10:52.504 --> 00:10:54.143
Especially if you're going to keep working as an assistant writer.

152
00:10:54.574 --> 00:10:55.913
Then I'll pay rent.

153
00:10:56.374 --> 00:10:58.844
Don't bother. You can just think of it as your own place.

154
00:10:59.783 --> 00:11:01.114
And you should start writing your own script.

155
00:11:01.584 --> 00:11:04.023
You can do some part-time jobs. It'd also be nice to be together.

156
00:11:05.754 --> 00:11:08.693
What's the point of writing? My work always fails to win competitions.

157
00:11:09.293 --> 00:11:10.793
I don't think I'm competent enough.

158
00:11:10.893 --> 00:11:12.893
No one knows that.

159
00:11:14.033 --> 00:11:16.033
I always doubted myself as well.

160
00:11:16.364 --> 00:11:19.163
Ms. Park told me that "The Man Who Eats Rare Steak" was terrible.

161
00:11:19.163 --> 00:11:21.933
But it won the competition. You were there too.

162
00:11:22.303 --> 00:11:23.374
You're right.

163
00:11:24.903 --> 00:11:27.214
Everything has its own right time. Your time will come.

164
00:11:27.744 --> 00:11:29.013
You just need to wait.

165
00:11:30.443 --> 00:11:32.513
Hyun Soo, you're the best.

166
00:11:32.913 --> 00:11:34.584
What should we eat for lunch?

167
00:11:37.084 --> 00:11:39.084
He's almost done with the dish.

168
00:11:39.084 --> 00:11:40.153
It smells great.

169
00:11:40.153 --> 00:11:43.594
Yes, it does. I'll go and have a taste.

170
00:11:43.663 --> 00:11:45.793
He's cooking bouillabaisse right now.

171
00:11:46.693 --> 00:11:49.364
I wonder how it'll taste.

172
00:11:50.533 --> 00:11:51.604
Why did you turn it off?

173
00:11:51.864 --> 00:11:53.834
You're so handsome.

174
00:11:54.033 --> 00:11:56.273
You're more handsome than most actors.

175
00:11:57.374 --> 00:12:00.173
Don't eat it yet. Wait until I give you the soup.

176
00:12:05.384 --> 00:12:06.813
I'm so jealous that you're young.

177
00:12:08.484 --> 00:12:10.984
You have a great future ahead of you.

178
00:12:11.454 --> 00:12:15.023
Do you know how proud I was in front of Daniel?

179
00:12:15.094 --> 00:12:16.393
You come to Seoul really often these days.

180
00:12:17.224 --> 00:12:19.124
That's because Daniel comes to Seoul often.

181
00:12:22.693 --> 00:12:23.864
You didn't season it right.

182
00:12:24.834 --> 00:12:25.864
I'm sure I did.

183
00:12:26.063 --> 00:12:28.834
Your taste buds aren't the same when you grow old.

184
00:12:29.803 --> 00:12:31.443
I'm not that old.

185
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:33.874
But everything else tastes great.

186
00:12:36.513 --> 00:12:37.913
You're a great person.

187
00:12:38.813 --> 00:12:40.614
Thank you for being born as my son.

188
00:12:47.653 --> 00:12:48.653
Where are you going?

189
00:12:48.653 --> 00:12:50.393
It's my day off, so I'm going to slack off.

190
00:12:50.763 --> 00:12:52.624
Can't you spend some time with me?

191
00:12:52.893 --> 00:12:53.994
Do you want to go shopping?

192
00:12:53.994 --> 00:12:55.334
You can go with Mr. Min.

193
00:12:55.464 --> 00:12:57.663
Can't you call him Professor Min?

194
00:12:57.663 --> 00:12:59.663
Do I need to call him that when he's not even here?

195
00:13:02.104 --> 00:13:05.244
Professor Min makes me happy.

196
00:13:05.874 --> 00:13:07.513
So please be nice to him.

197
00:13:08.374 --> 00:13:11.484
Someone told me that happiness comes from within.

198
00:13:11.584 --> 00:13:13.183
It doesn't come from someone else.

199
00:13:13.754 --> 00:13:15.413
It's time for you to grow up.

200
00:13:17.884 --> 00:13:19.124
I don't want to grow up.

201
00:13:19.994 --> 00:13:21.754
I've always lived my life like this. If I suddenly grow up,

202
00:13:22.053 --> 00:13:24.824
I'll suddenly feel too embarrassed of my past.

203
00:13:26.393 --> 00:13:27.763
You're so good with words.

204
00:13:37.244 --> 00:13:40.413
Hyun Soo, you seem awfully fine.

205
00:13:40.874 --> 00:13:42.374
It's difficult to come to a decision.

206
00:13:44.143 --> 00:13:45.844
But I've already made up my mind.

207
00:13:46.214 --> 00:13:48.413
You're really incredible.

208
00:13:48.584 --> 00:13:50.923
As soon as you make a decision, you just go for it.

209
00:13:52.354 --> 00:13:53.793
Let's go on a trip.

210
00:13:54.193 --> 00:13:55.653
You worked hard until now.

211
00:13:55.653 --> 00:13:59.624
Should I think of a place that's great for our current situation?

212
00:13:59.624 --> 00:14:00.634
Yes.

213
00:14:01.193 --> 00:14:04.403
The place where General Yi Sun Shin wrote "War Diary".

214
00:14:04.504 --> 00:14:05.504
- Yeosu! - Yeosu!

215
00:14:05.504 --> 00:14:06.933
We said the same thing!

216
00:14:07.874 --> 00:14:09.433
I'll look for a place to stay.

217
00:14:09.533 --> 00:14:10.604
Okay.

218
00:14:11.574 --> 00:14:13.744
My gosh, it's Director Kim.

219
00:14:13.913 --> 00:14:16.714
We shouldn't have told him the passcode in the first place.

220
00:14:16.884 --> 00:14:18.813
Hi, guys. What's that? Are you eating instant noodles?

221
00:14:18.913 --> 00:14:20.313
This is all we have.

222
00:14:21.283 --> 00:14:22.313
Hey, Ms. Hwangbo.

223
00:14:22.354 --> 00:14:23.984
Don't even think about asking her to do anything.

224
00:14:23.984 --> 00:14:25.954
Why do you keep asking her for favors?

225
00:14:25.984 --> 00:14:27.994
In my opinion, you need to start dating someone.

226
00:14:28.124 --> 00:14:29.324
You're so emotionally dry.

227
00:14:29.324 --> 00:14:31.023
How long has it been since you last dated anyone?

228
00:14:31.023 --> 00:14:32.594
What does dating have anything to do with this?

229
00:14:32.594 --> 00:14:34.693
Anyone would say that considering your temperament.

230
00:14:34.693 --> 00:14:36.393
What about Hyun Soo's temperament?

231
00:14:36.393 --> 00:14:38.263
It's a hundred times better than yours.

232
00:14:38.334 --> 00:14:41.604
Go! You're the Unit B director of "Unruly Detectives".

233
00:14:41.604 --> 00:14:43.033
How could you come here?

234
00:14:43.033 --> 00:14:44.043
You go girl!

235
00:14:44.273 --> 00:14:45.943
How funny.

236
00:14:45.943 --> 00:14:48.374
Jung Woo is having trouble with the network because of you.

237
00:14:51.513 --> 00:14:53.653
You're making this difficult, Mr. Park.

238
00:14:53.754 --> 00:14:56.153
You can't try to renegotiate the budget.

239
00:14:56.413 --> 00:14:59.754
You wanted me to sign the new writers team.

240
00:14:59.754 --> 00:15:01.893
The production company should cover that.

241
00:15:01.893 --> 00:15:03.893
Do you know how much we lost when our writer got fired?

242
00:15:03.893 --> 00:15:07.364
She wasn't fired. Writer Lee said she'd quit.

243
00:15:07.464 --> 00:15:10.663
Production companies sign with writers and then work with networks.

244
00:15:11.033 --> 00:15:12.903
What writer would want to work with us...

245
00:15:13.303 --> 00:15:15.433
if they hear we can't protect our own writers?

246
00:15:15.673 --> 00:15:18.574
Anyways, this issue is beyond me.

247
00:15:18.903 --> 00:15:20.474
Talk with the chief director.

248
00:15:23.074 --> 00:15:24.114
("Writer for 'Unruly Detectives' Replaced")

249
00:15:24.114 --> 00:15:27.454
Writer for "Unruly Detectives" Replaced.

250
00:15:27.854 --> 00:15:29.384
I knew this would happen.

251
00:15:30.484 --> 00:15:33.724
Writer Lee Hyun Soo had to drop out due to health concerns.

252
00:15:35.594 --> 00:15:36.893
As if.

253
00:15:41.293 --> 00:15:44.734
My skin's gotten dry pulling all those all-nighters.

254
00:15:44.734 --> 00:15:46.134
("Writer for 'Unruly Detectives' Replaced")

255
00:15:54.313 --> 00:15:56.043
I have to take it every day.

256
00:15:56.513 --> 00:15:59.543
I have to pull myself together if I don't want to end up like Hyun Soo.

257
00:16:00.783 --> 00:16:02.413
(Hong Ah)

258
00:16:06.254 --> 00:16:08.124
- Yes. - I was right.

259
00:16:08.423 --> 00:16:10.563
I said Hyun Soo would get fired.

260
00:16:10.964 --> 00:16:12.124
What are you going to do?

261
00:16:12.124 --> 00:16:14.793
She didn't get fired. She quit.

262
00:16:15.094 --> 00:16:17.634
Quitting or getting fired. It's basically the same thing.

263
00:16:17.634 --> 00:16:20.604
